      • getStationId

        public int getStationId()
        Get the station identifier.

        In this case, this is not a "weapon station" - see hardpoint. Instead it is the "payload station" in the sense used by STANAG 4586 (see AEP-84) for the stores management system (SMS).

        Returns:
        integer identifier for the station identifier

      • setStationId

        public void setStationId(int stationId)
        Set the station identifier.

        In this case, this is not a "weapon station" - see hardpoint. Instead it is the "payload station" in the sense used by STANAG 4586 (see AEP-84) for the stores management system (SMS).

        Parameters:
        stationId - integer identifier for the station identifier

      • getHardpointId

        public int getHardpointId()
        Get the hardpoint identifier.

        This corresponds to the aircraft hardpoint where the stores suspension equipment starts (e.g. a wing pylon, or bay location). Some platforms would call this a weapons station.

        Returns:
        the hardpoint identifier

      • setHardpointId

      • getCarriageId

      • isWeaponArmed

        public boolean isWeaponArmed()
        Check if weapon is armed in engagement status.

        ST0601 suggests this is "master arm", but it probably is intended to be weapon specific.

        Returns:
        true if weapon is armed, otherwise false
